{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WjBDJU9gqMDSiqbdYofAYA","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me create a detailed summary document:\n\n## Comprehensive Backflow Codebase Analysis\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of this Go-based background agent orchestrator. Here's the complete analysis:\n\n### 1. TASK MODEL (internal/models/task.go)\n\n**Core Task Structure:**\n- `ID`: String with `bf_` prefix (ULID-based, generated at creation time)\n- `Status`: Enum with states: pending → provisioning → running → completed|failed|interrupted|cancelled\n- `RepoURL`: GitHub repository URL (required)\n- `Branch`: Working branch name (defaults to backflow/${TASK_ID})\n- `TargetBranch`: Target for PR (defaults to main)\n- `Prompt`: Agent instruction (required)\n- `Context`: Additional context injected before prompt\n- `Model`: Claude model name (defaults to \"claude-sonnet-4-6\" from config)\n- `Effort`: Reasoning effort level - \"low\", \"medium\", \"high\", or \"xhigh\" (defaults to \"high\")\n- `MaxBudgetUSD`: Budget limit (only applies to api_key auth mode)\n- `MaxRuntimeMin`: Execution timeout in minutes\n- `MaxTurns`: Max conversation turns\n- `CreatePR`: Boolean flag for auto-PR creation\n- `PRTitle`, `PRBody`, `PRURL`: PR metadata\n- `AllowedTools`: Array of permitted Claude tools\n- `ClaudeMD`: Additional CLAUDE.md content to inject\n- `EnvVars`: Custom environment variables (map[string]string)\n- `InstanceID`, `ContainerID`: Track deployment location\n- `RetryCount`: Spot interruption retries\n- `CostUSD`, `Error`: Metadata\n- `CreatedAt`, `UpdatedAt`, `StartedAt`, `CompletedAt`: Timestamps\n\n**Validation (CreateTaskRequest.Validate):**\n- repo_url is required\n- prompt is required\n- max_budget_usd must be >= 0\n- max_runtime_min must be >= 0\n- effort must be one of: \"low\", \"medium\", \"high\", \"xhigh\" (case-sensitive)\n\n### 2. STORE INTERFACE & SQLite IMPLEMENTATION (internal/store/store.go, sqlite.go)\n\n**Store Interface Methods:**\n- `CreateTask(ctx context.Context, task *models.Task) error`\n- `GetTask(ctx context.Context, id string) (*models.Task, error)`\n- `ListTasks(ctx context.Context, filter TaskFilter) ([]*models.Task, error)`\n- `UpdateTask(ctx context.Context, task *models.Task) error`\n- `DeleteTask(ctx context.Context, id string) error`\n- Instance equivalents: CreateInstance, GetInstance, ListInstances, UpdateInstance\n\n**SQLite Implementation Details:**\n- Uses WAL mode for concurrency: `_journal_mode=WAL&_busy_timeout=5000&_foreign_keys=on`\n- Schema created on initialization (both tables auto-created if missing)\n- JSON serialization: `AllowedTools` and `EnvVars` stored as JSON strings\n- Boolean fields stored as 0/1 integers\n- Timestamps stored as RFC3339 strings\n- Indexes on status and created_at for query performance\n- Foreign key constraints enabled\n\n**Schema Tables:**\n- `tasks`: 28 columns storing all task fields\n- `instances`: Instance lifecycle tracking with running_containers count\n\n### 3. API HANDLERS (internal/api/handlers.go)\n\n**CreateTask Handler:**\n1. Parses JSON request (CreateTaskRequest)\n2. Validates input\n3. Creates Task with defaults from config:\n   - `Model`: Uses request value or config.DefaultModel\n   - `Effort`: Uses request value or config.DefaultEffort\n   - `MaxBudgetUSD`: Uses request value or config.DefaultMaxBudget\n   - `MaxRuntimeMin`: Uses request value or config.DefaultMaxRuntime (in minutes)\n   - `MaxTurns`: Uses request value or config.DefaultMaxTurns\n4. Generates unique ID: `bf_` + ULID\n5. Sets status to `pending`\n6. Stores in database\n7. Returns task in JSON envelope: `{data: {...}, error: \"\"}`\n\n**Other Endpoints:**\n- GET /api/v1/tasks/{id}: Fetch task by ID\n- GET /api/v1/tasks: List tasks (filterable by status, pagination)\n- DELETE /api/v1/tasks/{id}: Cancel running tasks or delete pending ones\n- GET /api/v1/tasks/{id}/logs: Fetch container logs from running instance\n- GET /api/v1/health: Health check with auth_mode\n\n**Response Format (internal/api/responses.go):**\nAll responses wrapped in envelope:\n```json\n{\n  \"data\": {...},\n  \"error\": \"\"\n}\n```\n\n### 4. ORCHESTRATOR (internal/orchestrator/)\n\n**Main Loop (orchestrator.go):**\n1. **Tick interval**: Configurable via BACKFLOW_POLL_INTERVAL_SEC (default 5s)\n2. **Three main operations per tick:**\n   - `monitorRunning()`: Check running tasks for completion/timeout\n   - `dispatchPending()`: Launch pending tasks on available instances\n   - `scaler.Evaluate()`: Handle instance scaling\n\n**Task Dispatch Flow:**\n1. Find instance with available container slots\n2. Update task status to `provisioning`\n3. Call `docker.RunAgent()` to start container\n4. Update task to `running` with container ID and StartedAt timestamp\n5. Increment running counter\n\n**Completion Handling:**\n- Detects via `InspectContainer()` checking docker state and status.json\n- Exit code 0 = completed\n- NeedsInput flag = agent asking clarifying questions\n- Non-zero exit or error string = failed\n- Fires webhook notifications\n- Updates instance container count\n\n**Timeout Enforcement:**\n- Checked in `monitorRunning()`\n- If current time > StartedAt + MaxRuntimeMin, kills the task\n\n**Docker Manager (docker.go):**\n\n**RunAgent Method (Critical for Configuration):**\n```\nEnvironment variables passed via docker run -e flags:\n- TASK_ID: Task ID\n- REPO_URL: Repository URL (shell-escaped)\n- BRANCH: Working branch\n- TARGET_BRANCH: Target branch\n- PROMPT: Main prompt (shell-escaped)\n- MODEL: Claude model name (shell-escaped) ← CRITICAL\n- EFFORT: Reasoning effort (shell-escaped) ← CRITICAL\n- MAX_BUDGET_USD: Budget (numeric)\n- MAX_TURNS: Turn limit (numeric)\n- CREATE_PR: Boolean string\n- PR_TITLE: (optional, shell-escaped)\n- PR_BODY: (optional, shell-escaped)\n- CLAUDE_MD: (optional, shell-escaped)\n- TASK_CONTEXT: Context from \"context\" field (shell-escaped)\n- AUTH_MODE: \"api_key\" or \"max_subscription\"\n- ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: API key (if api_key mode)\n- GITHUB_TOKEN: GitHub token (if provided)\n- Custom env vars from task.EnvVars (shell-escaped)\n```\n\nDocker run command structure:\n```bash\ndocker run -d --cpus=1 --memory=3g [volume-flags] [env-flags] backflow-agent\n```\n\n**Shell Escaping:**\n```go\nfunc shellEscape(s string) string {\n    return \"'\" + strings.ReplaceAll(s, \"'\", \"'\\\"'\\\"'\") + \"'\"\n}\n```\n\n**Container Inspection:**\n1. Runs docker inspect to get status and exit code\n2. Fetches last 20 lines of logs\n3. Attempts to copy `/home/agent/workspace/status.json` from container\n4. Parses status.json for:\n   - `needs_input`: Boolean\n   - `question`: String\n   - `complete`: Boolean\n   - `error`: String\n\n**SpotHandler (spot.go):**\n- Monitors for AWS spot interruption notices\n- Re-queues running tasks to pending status on interruption\n- Marks instance as draining\n- Increments RetryCount\n\n**Scaler (scaler.go):**\n- Launches new instances when capacity exhausted\n- Waits for SSM and Docker readiness\n- Scales down idle instances after 5 minutes\n- Max instances controlled by BACKFLOW_MAX_INSTANCES\n\n### 5. ENTRYPOINT SCRIPT (docker/entrypoint.sh)\n\n**Execution Flow:**\n1. **Configuration Phase:**\n   - Sources environment variables (sets defaults for missing vars)\n   - Validates AUTH_MODE (api_key or max_subscription)\n   \n2. **Clone & Setup Phase:**\n   ```bash\n   git clone --depth 50 <REPO_URL> <workspace>\n   git checkout <TARGET_BRANCH>\n   git checkout -b <BRANCH>\n   ```\n\n3. **Injection Phase:**\n   - Optionally injects CLAUDE_MD content into CLAUDE.md file\n   - Prepends TASK_CONTEXT to PROMPT if provided\n\n4. **Auth Phase:**\n   - GitHub token setup if provided\n   - Validates ANTHROPIC_API_KEY in api_key mode\n   - Validates ~/.claude exists in max_subscription mode\n   - Logs auth mode and model/effort level\n\n5. **Claude Execution Phase:**\n   ```bash\n   claude -p <PROMPT> \\\n           --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n           --model <MODEL> \\\n           --effort <EFFORT> \\\n           --max-turns <MAX_TURNS> \\\n           --output-format json \\\n           --verbose\n   ```\n   - Max 3 retry attempts on failure\n   - Appends error context to prompt on retry\n   - `--max-budget-usd` only added in api_key mode\n\n6. **Status Detection Phase:**\n   - Parses JSON output for success/failure\n   - Detects if agent needs input (keyword matching)\n   - Detects max_turns exceeded\n\n7. **Status File Writing:**\n   ```json\n   {\n     \"exit_code\": <code>,\n     \"complete\": <boolean>,\n     \"needs_input\": <boolean>,\n     \"question\": \"<string>\",\n     \"error\": \"<string>\"\n   }\n   ```\n\n8. **Git Push Phase:**\n   - `git add -A`\n   - Commits with message: \"backflow: agent work on task ${TASK_ID}\"\n   - Includes Model in commit message\n   - Includes Budget in commit message (api_key mode only)\n   - Force pushes with `--force-with-lease`\n\n9. **PR Creation Phase:**\n   - Auto-generates PR title if not provided\n   - Auto-generates PR body with task metadata\n   - Creates PR to target branch\n\n### 6. CONFIGURATION (internal/config/config.go)\n\n**Key Configuration Fields:**\n- `BACKFLOW_LISTEN_ADDR`: Server address (default: `:8080`)\n- `BACKFLOW_AUTH_MODE`: \"api_key\" or \"max_subscription\"\n- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`: Required for api_key mode\n- `CLAUDE_CREDENTIALS_PATH`: Path to .claude credentials for max_subscription\n- `AWS_REGION`: AWS region (default: us-east-1)\n- `BACKFLOW_INSTANCE_TYPE`: EC2 type (default: t4g.medium)\n- `BACKFLOW_AMI`: AMI ID (required)\n- `BACKFLOW_MAX_INSTANCES`: Max concurrent instances (default: 5)\n- `BACKFLOW_CONTAINERS_PER_INSTANCE`: Tasks per instance (default: 4)\n- `BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_MODEL`: Default Claude model (default: \"claude-sonnet-4-6\")\n- `BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_EFFORT`: Default effort (default: \"high\")\n- `BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_MAX_BUDGET`: Default budget (default: 10.0)\n- `BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_MAX_RUNTIME_MIN`: Default runtime in minutes (default: 30)\n- `BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_MAX_TURNS`: Default turns (default: 200)\n- `GITHUB_TOKEN`: GitHub PAT\n- `BACKFLOW_WEBHOOK_URL`: Webhook endpoint\n- `BACKFLOW_WEBHOOK_EVENTS`: Comma-separated event types to send\n- `BACKFLOW_DB_PATH`: SQLite database path (default: backflow.db)\n- `BACKFLOW_POLL_INTERVAL_SEC`: Orchestrator poll interval (default: 5)\n\n**Auth Modes:**\n- `api_key`: Concurrent tasks, billed per token, requires ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\n- `max_subscription`: Single concurrent task, requires ~/.claude credentials\n\n**Concurrency Calculation:**\n```go\nfunc (c *Config) MaxConcurrent() int {\n    if c.AuthMode == AuthModeMaxSubscription {\n        return 1\n    }\n    return c.MaxInstances * c.ContainersPerInst\n}\n```\n\n### 7. DOCKERFILE (docker/Dockerfile)\n\n**Base:** node:20-slim\n**Key Packages:** git, curl, ca-certificates, build-essential, python3, jq, gh CLI, Claude Code CLI\n**User:** agent (non-root, home at /home/agent)\n**Entry:** /home/agent/entrypoint.sh\n**Resource Limits:** 1 CPU, 3GB RAM (set in docker run command)\n\n### 8. RECENT CHANGES (Git History)\n\n**Latest Commit: 041bb4d** \"Merge pull request #7 from backflow-labs/feat/default-opus-high-effort\"\n- **6ed5002**: Fixed task ID extraction to use envelope response format\n- **3ddf636**: Fixed task ID extraction in create-task script\n- **13e62cf**: Logs model and reasoning effort in entrypoint output\n- **c30de2c**: Validates effort parameter and shell-escapes user-controlled env vars\n- **1337816**: Added effort parameter, defaulted to Opus with high reasoning effort\n\n### 9. CRITICAL CONFIGURATION POINTS FOR MODEL & EFFORT\n\n**Default Values (from config.go):**\n```go\nDefaultModel:  \"claude-sonnet-4-6\"  // via BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_MODEL env var\nDefaultEffort: \"high\"               // via BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_EFFORT env var\n```\n\n**Task Creation (handlers.go) - Uses withDefault helper:**\n```go\nModel:  withDefault(req.Model, h.config.DefaultModel)\nEffort: withDefault(req.Effort, h.config.DefaultEffort)\n```\n\n**Passed to Container (docker.go):**\n```go\nfmt.Sprintf(\"-e MODEL=%s\", shellEscape(task.Model))\nfmt.Sprintf(\"-e EFFORT=%s\", shellEscape(task.Effort))\n```\n\n**Used in Claude Command (entrypoint.sh):**\n```bash\nCLAUDE_ARGS=(\n    -p \"$FULL_PROMPT\"\n    --model \"$MODEL\"          # From environment\n    --effort \"$EFFORT\"        # From environment\n    # ... other args\n)\n```\n\n### 10. WEBHOOK NOTIFICATIONS (internal/notify/webhook.go)\n\n**Event Types:**\n- task.created, task.running, task.completed, task.failed, task.needs_input, task.interrupted\n\n**Event Structure:**\n```json\n{\n  \"event\": \"task.completed\",\n  \"task_id\": \"bf_...\",\n  \"repo_url\": \"...\",\n  \"prompt\": \"...\",\n  \"message\": \"...\",\n  \"agent_log_tail\": \"...\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-15T...\"\n}\n```\n\n**Retry Logic:** 3 attempts with exponential backoff (2s, 4s)\n\n### KEY FILES SUMMARY\n\n| File Path | Purpose |\n|-----------|---------|\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/models/task.go | Task struct, validation |\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/store/store.go | Store interface definition |\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/store/sqlite.go | SQLite implementation, schema, queries |\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/api/handlers.go | API endpoints, task creation logic |\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/api/server.go | Chi router setup |\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/api/responses.go | JSON envelope wrapper |\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go | Main polling loop, dispatch, monitoring |\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/orchestrator/docker.go | Docker container management via SSM |\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/orchestrator/scaler.go | Instance scaling logic |\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/orchestrator/spot.go | Spot interruption handling |\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/config/config.go | Environment variable configuration |\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/notify/webhook.go | Webhook notifications |\n| /home/agent/workspace/docker/Dockerfile | Agent container image definition |\n| /home/agent/workspace/docker/entrypoint.sh | Agent execution script, Claude invocation |\n| /home/agent/workspace/cmd/backflow/main.go | Server startup, goroutine initialization |\n| /home/agent/workspace/scripts/create-task.sh | CLI wrapper for task creation API |"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a70d56e155f4d7720 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 53951\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 49792</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2af19d51-84dc-4ce3-80b2-7d4b83aa4cbe","uuid":"db5b457a-76b0-41f1-a32f-276e3ff4eb42","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore this Go codebase to understand how tasks are created, stored, and executed. I need to understand:\n\n1. The Task model (fields, statuses, etc.) in internal/models/\n2. The Store interface and SQLite implementation in internal/store/\n3. The API handlers for task creation in internal/api/\n4. The orchestrator's docker execution in internal/orchestrator/ (especially docker.go and orchestrator.go)\n5. The entrypoint.sh in docker/ directory\n6. The config in internal/config/\n7. Any migration files or schema definitions\n8. The Dockerfile in docker/\n\nRead all relevant files completely. Pay special attention to:\n- How the model and reasoning effort are currently configured\n- How Docker containers are launched with environment variables\n- The full task creation flow from API to execution","agentId":"a70d56e155f4d7720","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me create a detailed summary document:\n\n## Comprehensive Backflow Codebase Analysis\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of this Go-based background agent orchestrator. Here's the complete analysis:\n\n### 1. TASK MODEL (internal/models/task.go)\n\n**Core Task Structure:**\n- `ID`: String with `bf_` prefix (ULID-based, generated at creation time)\n- `Status`: Enum with states: pending → provisioning → running → completed|failed|interrupted|cancelled\n- `RepoURL`: GitHub repository URL (required)\n- `Branch`: Working branch name (defaults to backflow/${TASK_ID})\n- `TargetBranch`: Target for PR (defaults to main)\n- `Prompt`: Agent instruction (required)\n- `Context`: Additional context injected before prompt\n- `Model`: Claude model name (defaults to \"claude-sonnet-4-6\" from config)\n- `Effort`: Reasoning effort level - \"low\", \"medium\", \"high\", or \"xhigh\" (defaults to \"high\")\n- `MaxBudgetUSD`: Budget limit (only applies to api_key auth mode)\n- `MaxRuntimeMin`: Execution timeout in minutes\n- `MaxTurns`: Max conversation turns\n- `CreatePR`: Boolean flag for auto-PR creation\n- `PRTitle`, `PRBody`, `PRURL`: PR metadata\n- `AllowedTools`: Array of permitted Claude tools\n- `ClaudeMD`: Additional CLAUDE.md content to inject\n- `EnvVars`: Custom environment variables (map[string]string)\n- `InstanceID`, `ContainerID`: Track deployment location\n- `RetryCount`: Spot interruption retries\n- `CostUSD`, `Error`: Metadata\n- `CreatedAt`, `UpdatedAt`, `StartedAt`, `CompletedAt`: Timestamps\n\n**Validation (CreateTaskRequest.Validate):**\n- repo_url is required\n- prompt is required\n- max_budget_usd must be >= 0\n- max_runtime_min must be >= 0\n- effort must be one of: \"low\", \"medium\", \"high\", \"xhigh\" (case-sensitive)\n\n### 2. STORE INTERFACE & SQLite IMPLEMENTATION (internal/store/store.go, sqlite.go)\n\n**Store Interface Methods:**\n- `CreateTask(ctx context.Context, task *models.Task) error`\n- `GetTask(ctx context.Context, id string) (*models.Task, error)`\n- `ListTasks(ctx context.Context, filter TaskFilter) ([]*models.Task, error)`\n- `UpdateTask(ctx context.Context, task *models.Task) error`\n- `DeleteTask(ctx context.Context, id string) error`\n- Instance equivalents: CreateInstance, GetInstance, ListInstances, UpdateInstance\n\n**SQLite Implementation Details:**\n- Uses WAL mode for concurrency: `_journal_mode=WAL&_busy_timeout=5000&_foreign_keys=on`\n- Schema created on initialization (both tables auto-created if missing)\n- JSON serialization: `AllowedTools` and `EnvVars` stored as JSON strings\n- Boolean fields stored as 0/1 integers\n- Timestamps stored as RFC3339 strings\n- Indexes on status and created_at for query performance\n- Foreign key constraints enabled\n\n**Schema Tables:**\n- `tasks`: 28 columns storing all task fields\n- `instances`: Instance lifecycle tracking with running_containers count\n\n### 3. API HANDLERS (internal/api/handlers.go)\n\n**CreateTask Handler:**\n1. Parses JSON request (CreateTaskRequest)\n2. Validates input\n3. Creates Task with defaults from config:\n   - `Model`: Uses request value or config.DefaultModel\n   - `Effort`: Uses request value or config.DefaultEffort\n   - `MaxBudgetUSD`: Uses request value or config.DefaultMaxBudget\n   - `MaxRuntimeMin`: Uses request value or config.DefaultMaxRuntime (in minutes)\n   - `MaxTurns`: Uses request value or config.DefaultMaxTurns\n4. Generates unique ID: `bf_` + ULID\n5. Sets status to `pending`\n6. Stores in database\n7. Returns task in JSON envelope: `{data: {...}, error: \"\"}`\n\n**Other Endpoints:**\n- GET /api/v1/tasks/{id}: Fetch task by ID\n- GET /api/v1/tasks: List tasks (filterable by status, pagination)\n- DELETE /api/v1/tasks/{id}: Cancel running tasks or delete pending ones\n- GET /api/v1/tasks/{id}/logs: Fetch container logs from running instance\n- GET /api/v1/health: Health check with auth_mode\n\n**Response Format (internal/api/responses.go):**\nAll responses wrapped in envelope:\n```json\n{\n  \"data\": {...},\n  \"error\": \"\"\n}\n```\n\n### 4. ORCHESTRATOR (internal/orchestrator/)\n\n**Main Loop (orchestrator.go):**\n1. **Tick interval**: Configurable via BACKFLOW_POLL_INTERVAL_SEC (default 5s)\n2. **Three main operations per tick:**\n   - `monitorRunning()`: Check running tasks for completion/timeout\n   - `dispatchPending()`: Launch pending tasks on available instances\n   - `scaler.Evaluate()`: Handle instance scaling\n\n**Task Dispatch Flow:**\n1. Find instance with available container slots\n2. Update task status to `provisioning`\n3. Call `docker.RunAgent()` to start container\n4. Update task to `running` with container ID and StartedAt timestamp\n5. Increment running counter\n\n**Completion Handling:**\n- Detects via `InspectContainer()` checking docker state and status.json\n- Exit code 0 = completed\n- NeedsInput flag = agent asking clarifying questions\n- Non-zero exit or error string = failed\n- Fires webhook notifications\n- Updates instance container count\n\n**Timeout Enforcement:**\n- Checked in `monitorRunning()`\n- If current time > StartedAt + MaxRuntimeMin, kills the task\n\n**Docker Manager (docker.go):**\n\n**RunAgent Method (Critical for Configuration):**\n```\nEnvironment variables passed via docker run -e flags:\n- TASK_ID: Task ID\n- REPO_URL: Repository URL (shell-escaped)\n- BRANCH: Working branch\n- TARGET_BRANCH: Target branch\n- PROMPT: Main prompt (shell-escaped)\n- MODEL: Claude model name (shell-escaped) ← CRITICAL\n- EFFORT: Reasoning effort (shell-escaped) ← CRITICAL\n- MAX_BUDGET_USD: Budget (numeric)\n- MAX_TURNS: Turn limit (numeric)\n- CREATE_PR: Boolean string\n- PR_TITLE: (optional, shell-escaped)\n- PR_BODY: (optional, shell-escaped)\n- CLAUDE_MD: (optional, shell-escaped)\n- TASK_CONTEXT: Context from \"context\" field (shell-escaped)\n- AUTH_MODE: \"api_key\" or \"max_subscription\"\n- ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: API key (if api_key mode)\n- GITHUB_TOKEN: GitHub token (if provided)\n- Custom env vars from task.EnvVars (shell-escaped)\n```\n\nDocker run command structure:\n```bash\ndocker run -d --cpus=1 --memory=3g [volume-flags] [env-flags] backflow-agent\n```\n\n**Shell Escaping:**\n```go\nfunc shellEscape(s string) string {\n    return \"'\" + strings.ReplaceAll(s, \"'\", \"'\\\"'\\\"'\") + \"'\"\n}\n```\n\n**Container Inspection:**\n1. Runs docker inspect to get status and exit code\n2. Fetches last 20 lines of logs\n3. Attempts to copy `/home/agent/workspace/status.json` from container\n4. Parses status.json for:\n   - `needs_input`: Boolean\n   - `question`: String\n   - `complete`: Boolean\n   - `error`: String\n\n**SpotHandler (spot.go):**\n- Monitors for AWS spot interruption notices\n- Re-queues running tasks to pending status on interruption\n- Marks instance as draining\n- Increments RetryCount\n\n**Scaler (scaler.go):**\n- Launches new instances when capacity exhausted\n- Waits for SSM and Docker readiness\n- Scales down idle instances after 5 minutes\n- Max instances controlled by BACKFLOW_MAX_INSTANCES\n\n### 5. ENTRYPOINT SCRIPT (docker/entrypoint.sh)\n\n**Execution Flow:**\n1. **Configuration Phase:**\n   - Sources environment variables (sets defaults for missing vars)\n   - Validates AUTH_MODE (api_key or max_subscription)\n   \n2. **Clone & Setup Phase:**\n   ```bash\n   git clone --depth 50 <REPO_URL> <workspace>\n   git checkout <TARGET_BRANCH>\n   git checkout -b <BRANCH>\n   ```\n\n3. **Injection Phase:**\n   - Optionally injects CLAUDE_MD content into CLAUDE.md file\n   - Prepends TASK_CONTEXT to PROMPT if provided\n\n4. **Auth Phase:**\n   - GitHub token setup if provided\n   - Validates ANTHROPIC_API_KEY in api_key mode\n   - Validates ~/.claude exists in max_subscription mode\n   - Logs auth mode and model/effort level\n\n5. **Claude Execution Phase:**\n   ```bash\n   claude -p <PROMPT> \\\n           --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n           --model <MODEL> \\\n           --effort <EFFORT> \\\n           --max-turns <MAX_TURNS> \\\n           --output-format json \\\n           --verbose\n   ```\n   - Max 3 retry attempts on failure\n   - Appends error context to prompt on retry\n   - `--max-budget-usd` only added in api_key mode\n\n6. **Status Detection Phase:**\n   - Parses JSON output for success/failure\n   - Detects if agent needs input (keyword matching)\n   - Detects max_turns exceeded\n\n7. **Status File Writing:**\n   ```json\n   {\n     \"exit_code\": <code>,\n     \"complete\": <boolean>,\n     \"needs_input\": <boolean>,\n     \"question\": \"<string>\",\n     \"error\": \"<string>\"\n   }\n   ```\n\n8. **Git Push Phase:**\n   - `git add -A`\n   - Commits with message: \"backflow: agent work on task ${TASK_ID}\"\n   - Includes Model in commit message\n   - Includes Budget in commit message (api_key mode only)\n   - Force pushes with `--force-with-lease`\n\n9. **PR Creation Phase:**\n   - Auto-generates PR title if not provided\n   - Auto-generates PR body with task metadata\n   - Creates PR to target branch\n\n### 6. CONFIGURATION (internal/config/config.go)\n\n**Key Configuration Fields:**\n- `BACKFLOW_LISTEN_ADDR`: Server address (default: `:8080`)\n- `BACKFLOW_AUTH_MODE`: \"api_key\" or \"max_subscription\"\n- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`: Required for api_key mode\n- `CLAUDE_CREDENTIALS_PATH`: Path to .claude credentials for max_subscription\n- `AWS_REGION`: AWS region (default: us-east-1)\n- `BACKFLOW_INSTANCE_TYPE`: EC2 type (default: t4g.medium)\n- `BACKFLOW_AMI`: AMI ID (required)\n- `BACKFLOW_MAX_INSTANCES`: Max concurrent instances (default: 5)\n- `BACKFLOW_CONTAINERS_PER_INSTANCE`: Tasks per instance (default: 4)\n- `BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_MODEL`: Default Claude model (default: \"claude-sonnet-4-6\")\n- `BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_EFFORT`: Default effort (default: \"high\")\n- `BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_MAX_BUDGET`: Default budget (default: 10.0)\n- `BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_MAX_RUNTIME_MIN`: Default runtime in minutes (default: 30)\n- `BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_MAX_TURNS`: Default turns (default: 200)\n- `GITHUB_TOKEN`: GitHub PAT\n- `BACKFLOW_WEBHOOK_URL`: Webhook endpoint\n- `BACKFLOW_WEBHOOK_EVENTS`: Comma-separated event types to send\n- `BACKFLOW_DB_PATH`: SQLite database path (default: backflow.db)\n- `BACKFLOW_POLL_INTERVAL_SEC`: Orchestrator poll interval (default: 5)\n\n**Auth Modes:**\n- `api_key`: Concurrent tasks, billed per token, requires ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\n- `max_subscription`: Single concurrent task, requires ~/.claude credentials\n\n**Concurrency Calculation:**\n```go\nfunc (c *Config) MaxConcurrent() int {\n    if c.AuthMode == AuthModeMaxSubscription {\n        return 1\n    }\n    return c.MaxInstances * c.ContainersPerInst\n}\n```\n\n### 7. DOCKERFILE (docker/Dockerfile)\n\n**Base:** node:20-slim\n**Key Packages:** git, curl, ca-certificates, build-essential, python3, jq, gh CLI, Claude Code CLI\n**User:** agent (non-root, home at /home/agent)\n**Entry:** /home/agent/entrypoint.sh\n**Resource Limits:** 1 CPU, 3GB RAM (set in docker run command)\n\n### 8. RECENT CHANGES (Git History)\n\n**Latest Commit: 041bb4d** \"Merge pull request #7 from backflow-labs/feat/default-opus-high-effort\"\n- **6ed5002**: Fixed task ID extraction to use envelope response format\n- **3ddf636**: Fixed task ID extraction in create-task script\n- **13e62cf**: Logs model and reasoning effort in entrypoint output\n- **c30de2c**: Validates effort parameter and shell-escapes user-controlled env vars\n- **1337816**: Added effort parameter, defaulted to Opus with high reasoning effort\n\n### 9. CRITICAL CONFIGURATION POINTS FOR MODEL & EFFORT\n\n**Default Values (from config.go):**\n```go\nDefaultModel:  \"claude-sonnet-4-6\"  // via BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_MODEL env var\nDefaultEffort: \"high\"               // via BACKFLOW_DEFAULT_EFFORT env var\n```\n\n**Task Creation (handlers.go) - Uses withDefault helper:**\n```go\nModel:  withDefault(req.Model, h.config.DefaultModel)\nEffort: withDefault(req.Effort, h.config.DefaultEffort)\n```\n\n**Passed to Container (docker.go):**\n```go\nfmt.Sprintf(\"-e MODEL=%s\", shellEscape(task.Model))\nfmt.Sprintf(\"-e EFFORT=%s\", shellEscape(task.Effort))\n```\n\n**Used in Claude Command (entrypoint.sh):**\n```bash\nCLAUDE_ARGS=(\n    -p \"$FULL_PROMPT\"\n    --model \"$MODEL\"          # From environment\n    --effort \"$EFFORT\"        # From environment\n    # ... other args\n)\n```\n\n### 10. WEBHOOK NOTIFICATIONS (internal/notify/webhook.go)\n\n**Event Types:**\n- task.created, task.running, task.completed, task.failed, task.needs_input, task.interrupted\n\n**Event Structure:**\n```json\n{\n  \"event\": \"task.completed\",\n  \"task_id\": \"bf_...\",\n  \"repo_url\": \"...\",\n  \"prompt\": \"...\",\n  \"message\": \"...\",\n  \"agent_log_tail\": \"...\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-15T...\"\n}\n```\n\n**Retry Logic:** 3 attempts with exponential backoff (2s, 4s)\n\n### KEY FILES SUMMARY\n\n| File Path | Purpose |\n|-----------|---------|\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/models/task.go | Task struct, validation |\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/store/store.go | Store interface definition |\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/store/sqlite.go | SQLite implementation, schema, queries |\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/api/handlers.go | API endpoints, task creation logic |\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/api/server.go | Chi router setup |\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/api/responses.go | JSON envelope wrapper |\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go | Main polling loop, dispatch, monitoring |\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/orchestrator/docker.go | Docker container management via SSM |\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/orchestrator/scaler.go | Instance scaling logic |\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/orchestrator/spot.go | Spot interruption handling |\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/config/config.go | Environment variable configuration |\n| /home/agent/workspace/internal/notify/webhook.go | Webhook notifications |\n| /home/agent/workspace/docker/Dockerfile | Agent container image definition |\n| /home/agent/workspace/docker/entrypoint.sh | Agent execution script, Claude invocation |\n| /home/agent/workspace/cmd/backflow/main.go | Server startup, goroutine initialization |\n| /home/agent/workspace/scripts/create-task.sh | CLI wrapper for task creation API |"}],"totalDurationMs":49792,"totalTokens":53951,"totalToolUseCount":20,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4726,"cache_read_input_tokens":45016,"output_tokens":4203,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4726},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
